    "body": "Hmm it looks like it is running out of memory for some reason. Do you happen to be on a machine with very little memory? Also, you shouldn't use `sudo` when installing Truffle as it can cause all sorts of permissions issues. You should probably use npm with a Node version manager like nvm which is what npm recommends. See [this npm article](https://docs.npmjs.com/resolving-eacces-permissions-errors-when-installing-packages-globally).",
